Job Description
InterScripts is seeking 1 candidate as a SQL Developer/Data Analyst.
BACKGROUND INFORMATION
The InterScripts customer is located in Annapolis, Maryland, and is comprised of six units including application development and support, hardware installation and maintenance, operation of the Data Center computer systems, and support of online case management and business applications at the District and Circuit Courts across the state.
RESOURCE QUALIFICATIONS
1. The Candidate shall have one (1) year of experience consulting services.
2. The Candidate shall propose a resource that meets the following minimum qualifications:
a. Active Oracle PL/SQL certification,
b. Twelve (12) or more years of SQL programming experience, and
c. Twelve (12) or more years of PL/SQL programming experience.
SCOPE OF WORK
Candidate proposed resource shall be responsible for the following:
1. Analyzing, testing, debugging and repairing existing PL/SQL based applications.
2. Analyzing new business rules and interfaces in order to design and implement new Oracle objects.
3. Preparing and maintaining documentation on new and existing data models.
4. Preparing and maintaining documentation for new and existing programming objects.
5. Packaging and configuring Oracle object components for deployment across Development, Test and Production Database Environments.
6. Working with Architects and Oracle DBA staff to establish standards for developing and deploying Oracle objects.
7. Assisting Business Intelligence staff with reporting requirements and solutions.
8. Collaborating with stakeholders across different business units to align data initiatives with business strategies.
9. Evaluating and enhancing SQL performance.
10. Preparing regular and ad hoc reports, including:
a. Weekly project report of progress and status,
b. Weekly time report, and
c. Additional reports as requested.
CANDIDATE RESOURCE(S) SKILLS, EXPERIENCE, & CAPABILITIES
1. Candidate shall possess the following preferred skills, experience, and capabilities:
a. The ability to: (1) Break down complex programming concepts into organized and concise units. (2) Work in an agile, self-motivated environment with multiple, concurrent priorities.
b. An understanding of relational data concepts and the ability to apply these concepts to concrete solutions.
c. Development skills with Oracle PL/SQL (Packages, Functions, Procedures, triggers), Materialized Views, DBLinks, and Oracle Jobs.
d. Strong analytical skills for evaluating, documenting, and enhancing existing and new data models.
e. Experience with:
(1) Reverse Engineering and Refactoring PL/SQL code,
(2) Extraction, Transform and Load programming,
(3) Data Warehouse/ Data Mart design,
(4) Asynchronous event-driven applications.
f. Knowledge of the following:
(1) BI Publisher,
(2) Java syntax,
(3) SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS),
(4) XML syntax and parsing,
(5) Domain knowledge of court related concepts and business activities.
PLACE OF PERFORMANCE
1. Work shall be performed in a hybrid setting as follows:
a. Three (3) days remote at a suitable off-site location selected by the Candidate/Candidate Resource.
(1) InterScripts reserves the right to determine an off-site location is not suitable (e.g., crowded public space with distracting background noise during meetings).
b. Two (2) days on site at the Maryland Judiciary Information Systems, 189 Harry S Truman Parkway, Annapolis, MD 21401.
2. Additional on-site support may be required, to manage production application issues, security threats, or critical initiatives.
a. As designated by the customer’s Chief Technology Officer, the contractor must be able to report on-site within four (4) hours after notification.
(1) If required to report, the Candidate Resource shall report to Maryland Judiciary Information Systems, 189 Harry S Truman Parkway, Annapolis, MD 21401.
3. The customer reserves the right to regularly evaluate performance and withdraw remote privileges in the event of a decline in contractual performance.

Under direction from the Director of Analytics and Institutional Research, Data Analysts at the College of Southern Idaho (CSI) support a campus-wide data-informed decision-making culture. By querying data and creating reports, the Data Analyst provides insights that help the business make decisions. The Data Analyst also looks for patterns in the data that can improve student outcomes and increase the CSI’s student body through retention and recruiting analytics.

THIS IS NOT A REMOTE POSITION, AND THE SUCCESSFUL APPLICANT WILL BE WORKING ON CAMPUS IN TWIN FALLS, IDAHO.

The Data Analysts are responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting on data from various internal and external sources. They know how to validate data and find data integrity issues that arise during the data cleaning process. Analysts provide BI solutions and use reporting techniques that adhere to sound research principles.

Proactively developing and maintaining good relationships with stakeholders across the organization is essential for Data Analysts. They need to deliver quality solutions that meet their stakeholders’ expectations. This requires working independently, collaborating, and engaging within the college’s institutional effectiveness (IE) team with administrators, faculty, and staff from across the college.

Analysts should be curious, critical thinkers who desire to develop and enhance their technical skillset. Successful analysts can balance a high-level perspective of business problems with the technical details needed to provide solutions. They demonstrate some degree of “business sense,” with the ability to think in terms of the administrators they are assisting while at the same time maintaining a more in-depth understanding of the data and related technical components needed to address the problem.

Data Analyst Duties & Responsibilities

Project requirements vary but will likely require a combination of some or all of the following:

Support a campus-wide data-informed decision-making culture.
Work with stakeholders to establish and define actionable research questions.
Implement actionable analytics with a focus on recruiting and retention efforts.
Create and organize various student contact lists, allowing CSI staff to execute strategic student outreach effectively.
Build and maintain business intelligence reports and dashboards.
Anticipate the need for and suggest reports and queries relating to the institutional mission.
Compile, analyze, and report institutional data related to various student and institutional characteristics.
Research, organize, and assemble data retrieved from various local, state, and national databases.
Manage survey projects from design through analysis and reporting.
Produce actionable insights from data through various quantitative and qualitative analytics.
Develop presentations and visualizations that effectively communicate report outcomes and key findings.

Collaboration and teamwork
Exemplify quality customer service, client relations, and time management.
Handle correspondence and communications in a professional and timely manner.
Work effectively both independently and collaboratively with colleagues.
Actively participate in weekly Institutional Research meetings to discuss current projects, challenges, and successes.
Collaborate with Institutional Technology (IT) and other stakeholders across the institutions to define business processes that maintain and enhance data integrity.
Emphasize reproducibility of research through thorough documentation and transparency.

Additional responsibilities
Engage in consistent learning, development, and improvement.
Identify and master new technical tools and techniques that enhance department skill sets.
Maintain office files, records, and software logs, emphasizing reproducibility.
Perform other miscellaneous and special duties as assigned.

Required Qualifications/Skills

Education and Experience
Hold an associate’s degree in business, analytics, economics, finance, or a related field.
Have at least one year of relevant experience, which can include internships, extracurricular activities, or volunteer work.
Technical Knowledge
Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite (Outlook, Word, PowerPoint, Excel).
Proficiency with Power BI
Functional skills with SQL (e.g., filtering, using the HAVING clause, and merging data using inner and outer joins)
Basic statistics.

Ability to work in both team and independent work environments.
Excellent communication and client management skills.

aytm delivers state-of-the-art insights automation technology and expert guidance that’s focused on providing answers for the clients of today, while evolving a platform that supports the curious of tomorrow. Experience using one or more online survey platforms. Experience with the aytm platform is preferred, but not required.
Strong written and verbal skills and should enjoy taking a consultative and collaborative approach – both with clients and fellow team members.

We’re a fun and vibrant group of people, dedicated to putting in the hard work to make a platform we are proud of, serving the needs of our clients with empathy, and making aytm an incredible place to work. POSITION SUMMARY
The Empire State Building Observatory (ESBO) is seeking a Revenue Data Analyst to join the Revenue Management team. Your primary responsibility will be to analyze large datasets, extract meaningful insights, and present actionable recommendations to the leadership team. You will collaborate with various departments to identify opportunities for revenue growth, track key performance indicators (KPIs), and contribute to the overall success of the company. You will leverage your expertise in data analysis, business intelligence, and revenue management to shape ESBO’s total revenue strategies and streamline efficiencies to make better and faster decisions. As a key player in our organization, you will be responsible for tactical execution of revenue maximization through data analytics and trend analysis. Your strong leadership, analytical skills, and business acumen will be instrumental in shaping our market presence and driving sustainable success.

RESPONSIBILITIES
Data Gathering and Modeling
Ensure data integrity and consistency across systems, identifying and resolving data discrepancies as needed.
Implement data quality controls and continuously improve data management processes.
Conduct regular data quality checks to identify and rectify data discrepancies and anomalies. Implement data governance practices to maintain data accuracy and compliance with relevant regulations.
Create and maintain reports, dashboards, and data visualizations to present key performance indicators (KPIs) and business metrics. Customize reporting based on user needs to ensure stakeholders have access to actionable insights.
Utilize data analytics tools (e.g., SQL, SSRS, Excel, Python, Tableau, Power BI) to manipulate and analyze data efficiently.
Develop data models to streamline data integration and transformation processes. Ensure data accuracy, consistency, and integrity through data cleansing and normalization techniques.
Create and maintain data dashboards, reports, and visualization tools to present key performance indicators (KPIs) and track the effectiveness of commercial initiatives. Provide regular reports to senior management to support strategic decision-making.
Data Analysis and Interpretation
Collect and organize large datasets from multiple sources, ensuring data integrity and accuracy.
Conduct thorough analyses to identify patterns, trends, and correlations within the data.
Translate complex data into clear and insightful reports, dashboards, and visualizations.
Oversee the collection, integration, and validation of commercial data from various sources, ensuring data quality and integrity. Perform sophisticated data analysis to derive actionable insights, market trends, and customer behavior patterns.
Provide insights for daily, weekly, monthly, and quarterly reporting.
Balance occupancy and average ticket price for each sales channel to ensure total revenue optimization.
Participate and support in the budgeting and forecasting processes.
Utilize statistical and predictive modeling techniques to forecast revenue trends and outcomes.
Evaluate the performance of commercial initiatives, product launches, and marketing campaigns by developing metrics, tracking progress, and recommending improvements to enhance revenue generation and market share.
Revenue Optimization
Leverage developed tools to optimize revenues through capacity management, segmentation, pricing, and upsells.
Identify revenue growth opportunities, develop strategies, and support the implementation of revenue-related initiatives.
Utilize historical data and trend analysis to develop forecasts and predictive models that assist in resource planning, inventory management, and business performance evaluation.
Product and Pricing Strategy
Work closely with product development teams to align product offerings with market demands. Develop pricing strategies that optimize revenue and market competitiveness while considering customer value perception.
Market and Competitive Analysis
Monitor city-wide trends, relating to inbound NYC travel, trends, consumer mix, competitor pricing, and competitor products.
Conduct market research and competitor analysis to identify industry trends and potential opportunities.
Provide insights on market dynamics and competitive landscape to support strategic decision-making.
Conduct comprehensive market research and competitive analysis to assess market trends, customer needs, and industry dynamics. Utilize data-driven insights to identify new market segments and capitalize on emerging opportunities.
Conduct thorough market research and competitive analysis to identify growth opportunities, market trends, and potential risks. Utilize external data sources to augment internal datasets and gain a comprehensive understanding of the industry landscape.
Stay up-to-date with industry trends, regulatory changes, and technological advancements that may impact the company's commercial activities. Share industry insights and best practices with the team to drive continuous improvement.
Stay updated with industry best practices, advancements in BI technologies, and emerging data analysis techniques. Propose and implement process improvements to optimize BI workflows.
Collaboration
Collaborate with various teams, including sales, marketing, finance, and operations, to gather data requirements and understand business needs.
Communicate data-driven insights and recommendations to stakeholders in a clear and concise manner.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify data requirements and extract relevant information from various sources, including databases, spreadsheets, and external APIs. Perform in-depth data analysis using SQL, Excel, or other data analysis tools to uncover trends, patterns, and anomalies.
Collaborate with sales and marketing teams to ensure seamless execution of commercial strategies. Provide data-driven insights to support sales efforts and marketing campaigns, enhancing the overall effectiveness of commercial initiatives.
WHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE
Develop SOP’s and reports to streamline processes, manage day-to-day operations, and increase revenues.
Evaluate unconstrained demand and determine price elasticity by sales channel to determine the optimal mix.
Provide recommendations regarding pricing, product types, data capture opportunities, and segmentation mix.
Solid understanding of commercial operations, market dynamics, and sales strategies. Ability to align data insights with business objectives.
Assess new business developments for incremental revenue opportunities.
Build a long-term holistic revenue strategy to optimize revenues for ESBO.
Ability to thrive in a dynamic and evolving market landscape, adjusting strategies to meet changing business conditions.

REQUIRED SKILLS/ ABILITIES
Data analytics tools experience required (e.g., SQL, SSRS, Excel, Python, Tableau, Power BI).
Experience with data analysis, streamlining complex information, finance, and revenue management.
Ability to work with complex datasets and extract actionable insights.
Exceptional written and oral communication skills.
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities, with a proven track record of translating data into actionable business strategies.
Proven ability to drive results, meet deadlines, and exceed targets in a fast-paced and competitive environment.
Detail-oriented with a focus on data accuracy and quality.
Strong business acumen and understanding of revenue drivers.
Proficiency in sales technology and CRM software.
Excellent multi-tasking, organizational, and time management skills.

EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE
Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Finance, Economics, Computer Science, or Statistics.
Three to five years of experience in a related position.
Must have experience with creating reports and models.
Ability to automate processes and streamline efficiencies.

Department Overview
Electric Asset Management is responsible for the electric system engineering and planning, asset strategy, and risk management across transmission, distribution, and substation asset families. This centralized, risk-informed approach allows PG&E to manage electric risk, asset and system health, interconnections, and performance by using consistent standards, work methods, prioritization, and program sponsorship, while leveraging lessons learned from inspections and asset data to inform asset management decisions. The organization is accountable for asset planning and strategy, standards and work methods, and asset data management for Electric.

The Asset Knowledge Management (AKM) team, within Electric Asset Management, is responsible for the management, quality, and access of PG&E’s electric asset data. The team’s objective is to maximize the use and ensure the trustworthiness of PG&E’s critical electric data assets.

Position Summary
The Expert Data Quality Analyst will be responsible for technical implementation of the Asset Data Quality (ADQ) program – a mission critical program launched in 2022 to systematically achieve and maintain the level of data quality required to support Electric Engineering Planning & Strategy’s business objectives, including regulatory compliance, risk management, improved operational efficiency, and advanced analytics. Program objectives include establishing a comprehensive inventory of PG&E’s critical electric asset-related data, capturing and maintaining metadata for all critical data, establishing and applying data quality rules to all critical data, and prioritizing data quality issues for remediation.

The Expert Data Quality Analyst will work at the direction of the ADQ Program Manager and partner with a cross-functional team composed of members from Electric Asset Knowledge Management, Electric Asset Management, Enterprise Data Management, Information Technology to implement the ADQ program. Responsibilities include leading the collection of metadata, development of data quality rules, guidance of data quality platform architecture decisions, conducting cause analysis regarding data quality rule violations, and supporting data quality remediation activities.

The near-term focus of ADQ will be on systematic measurement and improvement of PG&E’s electric Asset Registry and Asset Condition data. The ADQ program will expand its focus will shift to other data types that support Asset Management (e.g., event data, maintenance).

This position is hybrid, working from your remote office and your assigned work location based on business need. The assigned work location will be within the PG&E Service Territory.

Partner with lead Program Manager to implement Asset Data Quality (ADQ) programs to systematically inventory PG&E’s critical electric asset data, capture metadata, measure data quality, and drive the execution of high-priority data improvements.
Build strong relationships with business data stewards, asset data system specialists, IT Foundry ontology team, IT data quality team and IT architecture team to facilitate program implementation.
For critical datasets, lead the documentation of metadata in Collibra, integration of data into Foundry, development of data quality rules and guide development of dashboards to monitor data quality

Continuously monitor data quality rule performance to ensure that rules are functional and triage/remediate data quality rule errors when they arise.
Partner with Business Data Stewards to update, modify or add data quality rules.
Ensure data quality action plans are implemented where data fails to meet established data governance standards.
Advise Program Manager on strategy and roadmap to reflect continuous improvement and expansion into data types beyond Asset Registry and Asset Condition data (e.g., event data)
Technical Skills - MS Excel, Python, Foundry, Collibra, PowerBI, PowerApps, SharePoint Online, SQL etc.

Job Title: Employee Insights Data Analyst, Senior Associate
Job Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

Our Employee Insights team studies employee interactions, trends and changes to better understand our employees’ experiences. Usually, we begin with a question, challenge or idea related to our company’s workforce trends. Your role involves taking those hypotheses and determining how to best understand them through structured research and data analysis.
Your primary responsibility will be gathering, analyzing, and presenting data about employee experience and workforce trends, in partnership with key stakeholders to deliver unique insights about the organization.
This position reports to the VP of Reporting and Analytics and will be part of a team of problem solvers and solution designers dedicated to making Chase a great place to work.
Our job is to dig into the trends, changes and nuances that exist amongst Consumer and Community Banking’s global population. The journey often starts with a hypothesis or a question. Your job will be to collect, synthesize, and present data we need to dig in to key research topics, and to maintain responsibility for tracking and reporting on key metrics that inform senior leaders decision making processes.
Job Responsibilities:
Act as the voice of the employee by supporting the design and implementation of our listening strategy and by providing high quality employee insights that HR and Business Leaders can leverage to influence the employee experience
Conduct end-to-end analysis on large employee data sets to identify patterns/trends and answer questions/hypothesis about the employee experience and what influences it
Turn data into easy to understand visuals that tell a story. Make complex ideas simple so leaders can act on them
Be an expert project manager of all efforts you touch, delivering high quality work on time consistently
Ensure all appropriate data privacy, security, and controls requirements are incorporated into all processes
Maintain and expand partnerships with key stakeholders within the lines of business and at the firmwide level
Required Qualifications, capabilities and skills
5+ years of relevant work experience, preferably in a role involving extracting/ aggregating data and performing employee data analysis and storytelling
Advanced knowledge of analyzing both structured and unstructured data; managing and manipulate large data sets in Excel; quantitative and qualitative research
Ability to work to solve problems independently, remove barriers and propose solutions, i.e. taking a hypothesis, researching and coming back with a perspective
Ability to identify and communicate critical insights through appealing and concise reports and summaries
Strong partnership and consulting skills, ability to work with a variety of stakeholders and peers in order to get things done
Balance of intellectual curiosity with exceptional critical thinking, problem solving and analytical skills; ability to absorb and present complex ideas quickly and accurately
Preferred Qualifications, capabilities and skills
Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Statistics, Data Science, Industrial and Organizational Psychology, or other Behavioral Sciences
5+ years of specific HR systems experience
Experience with R, Python or other statistical programming languages/software, Business Intelligence software and/or data wrangling tools such as Alteryx
Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau or QlikView

Chase is a leading financial services firm, helping nearly half of America’s households and small businesses achieve their financial goals through a broad range of financial products. Our mission is to create engaged, lifelong relationships and put our customers at the heart of everything we do. We also help small businesses, nonprofits and cities grow, delivering solutions to solve all their financial needs.

Position Summary

The Data Exploitation Analyst participates in all phases of data collection, processing, and reporting at a customer site in Suitland, MD. The primary responsibilities of this role are to acquire, analyze, compile, evaluate, and review data for use in standard products, non-standard products, and/or data holdings in support of mission requirements.
Duties & Responsibilities
Processing, analysis, evaluation and exploitation of navigation, remote sensor, and shipboard instrumentation data collected from various deep ocean systems.
The candidate will be involved in pre-mission support, data collection, analyst & evaluation, and report generation.
As enhanced data is identified, the candidate will be responsible to update and correct data sets.
Perform analysis and evaluation of imagery collected from side scan sonar, bathometric, video, and still photography cameras.
Use proprietary software including GIS-based systems in a network of workstations and personal computers (Windows) to perform basic imaging enhancement, display, and analytical functions to obtain, organize, and present information relevant to the exploitation of remotely sensed and imaged data obtained from deep ocean systems.
Review mission related data logs, worksheets, and reports to determine focal points for the analysis as well as discovery of deficiencies and discrepancies in the performance of data collection equipment and systems.
Preparation of formal written technical reports as well as oral briefs to report analysis findings and conclusions to the customer.
Schedule can be demanding throughout the year and work outside normal working hours from time to time should be anticipated.
Travel is required. Will be required to participate in at sea exercises or data collection missions of various durations. Durations normally are between 30-60 days but can be as much as 90 days. Normal annual requirement is 120 days.
Represent OTECH and our customer by interacting and participating in meetings, panels, and committees within Department of Defense, Department of the Navy, and Intelligence Community in the capital planning process
Production of various ad hoc documentation & deliverables.
Maintain configuration control thereby ensuring precise data records.
Support program reviews and technical reviews of various documentation deliverables.

Associate degree in a technical or related field. Equivalent work experience may be considered in lieu of degree.
Minimum three to five years of related experience.
Background in GIS products (ESRI) and Side Look Sonars (SLS) processing.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office, including Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, and Excel.
Ability to obtain and maintain a DoD security clearance is required. Must hold/acquire a TS/SCI with Polygraph.
Strong written and verbal communication skills.

DESIRED
Bachelor’s degree in Oceanography, Underwater Archeology, or related field.

Knowledge of products like SonarWiz, Hypack and WinFrog.

Job Title: Micro-Tasker on Toloka
Job Overview:
We are seeking highly motivated individuals to join our team as Micro-Taskers on Toloka. As a Micro-Tasker, you will be responsible for completing small, quick tasks on the Toloka platform. These tasks may include image labeling, text categorization, data verification, sentiment analysis, and more. This is a flexible, remote position that allows you to work at your own pace and earn money based on the number of tasks completed.
Responsibilities:
- Access the Toloka platform and select available micro-tasks to complete.
- Follow the instructions provided for each task accurately and efficiently.
- Perform tasks such as image labeling, text categorization, data verification, sentiment analysis, and other similar activities.
- Maintain a high level of accuracy and attention to detail while completing tasks.
- Meet or exceed task completion targets and quality standards set by the task requester.
- Communicate effectively with the task requester, if necessary, to clarify instructions or seek additional information.
- Work independently and efficiently, managing your own time and prioritizing tasks effectively.
- Report any technical issues or bugs encountered while working on the Toloka platform.
Requirements:
- Excellent attention to detail and ability to follow instructions accurately.
- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
- Good command of the English language, both written and spoken.
- Reliable internet connection and access to a computer or smartphone.
- Ability to work independently and manage your own time effectively.
- Prior experience with micro-tasking platforms like Toloka is a plus but not required.
Benefits:
- Flexible working hours: You can work anytime, anywhere, as long as there are available tasks.
- Work from home: This is a remote position that allows you to work from the comfort of your own home.
- Competitive pay: You will be compensated based on the number of tasks completed.
- Skill development: Micro-tasking on Toloka provides an opportunity to develop and enhance your analytical and problem-solving skills.
- Opportunity for growth: Exceptional performers may have the opportunity to take on more complex tasks or even become task reviewers in the future.
If you are detail-oriented, enjoy working independently, and want to earn money by completing small, quick tasks, then this role as a Micro-Tasker on Toloka is perfect for you. Apply now and join our team!

The Role
As a Senior Healthcare Data Analyst on the SafeMine Product Team, you will own analyses and projects focused on evaluating and integrating large healthcare datasets (Rx, Mx, EHR) from external sources. Data is central to the success of our products – both in quality and coverage. These datasets will be used downstream as a critical component of our analytics and data products.
You will be responsible for analyzing and evaluating prospective new healthcare datasets in terms of their content, completeness, gaps, and how they complement existing datasets. Your evaluations will be used to determine whether to license these datasets.
For datasets that are already licensed, you will work closely with product managers on the SafeMine Product Team to configure the software to ingest and process the data. SafeMine is a big data health care de-identification software platform that powers Veeva’s Compass and Crossix Analytics product lines.
You will assess data to ensure fields conform to standard formats and contain core elements. You will be responsible for communicating follow-up questions to data suppliers. You will identify gaps in new and existing data and work with developers on transformation and mapping logic. You’ll be responsible for communicating your findings to internal stakeholders, providing recommendations on any findings, and designing product and data enhancements where needed.
This is a great opportunity for someone who is passionate about data analytics and excited to bring that knowledge to dozens of healthcare data integrations.
What You’ll Do
Explore and derive insights from high volumes of inbound health data to ensure accuracy, completeness, reliability, relevance, and timeliness
Execute data querying, cleansing, and analysis. Understand the impact of missing values, recognize discrepancies, and apply methods for deduplication
Conduct analysis and field mapping on data from potential new data sources under consideration to assess integration into the data network
Perform data investigations and exploratory analysis to focus on continuous improvement of our Veeva Compass and Crossix Analytics suite of products
Build expertise on a wide range of health data, contributing to documentation and validation reports
Perform exploratory analytics to find data issues and provide recommendations for fixing
Test changes in the data (both planned and unplanned) to determine the impact on customers
Build new attributes for both internal and customer-facing use, to continue to improve the usability of the data
Collaborate closely with a team of Product Managers, Data Operations, and Developers to ensure data is built and delivered with quality
Your work will inform the direction of multi-million-dollar data investment decisions
Requirements
4+ years of industry experience working with big healthcare datasets (prescription and medical claims)
Proficient in SQL and Excel
Knowledge of industry-standard billing codes such as ICD, CPT/HCPCS, NDC
Understand how relational databases work, and experience designing transformations, mappings, and working with reference tables
Experience investigating data issues and working with a cross-functional team for addressing
Experience with visualization tools such as Tableau or Spotfire
Energized by working through complex problems and bringing innovation to products
BA/BS degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Math, or a related technical field
Comfortable presenting findings to internal executive stakeholders
Nice to Have
Experience in Python
Experience working with clinical (EHR/EMR) data
Experience working with AWS
Experience in the Life Sciences industry
Experience working within an agile team

THIS IS NOT A REMOTE POSITION, AND THE SUCCESSFUL APPLICANT WILL BE WORKING ON CAMPUS IN TWIN FALLS, IDAHO.

The Data Analysts are responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting on data from various internal and external sources. They know how to validate data and find data integrity issues that arise during the data cleaning process. Analysts provide BI solutions and use reporting techniques that adhere to sound research principles.

Proactively developing and maintaining good relationships with stakeholders across the organization is essential for Data Analysts. They need to deliver quality solutions that meet their stakeholders’ expectations. This requires working independently, collaborating, and engaging within the college’s institutional effectiveness (IE) team with administrators, faculty, and staff from across the college.

Analysts should be curious, critical thinkers who desire to develop and enhance their technical skillset. Successful analysts can balance a high-level perspective of business problems with the technical details needed to provide solutions. They demonstrate some degree of “business sense,” with the ability to think in terms of the administrators they are assisting while at the same time maintaining a more in-depth understanding of the data and related technical components needed to address the problem.

GRAIL is a healthcare company whose mission is to detect cancer early, when it can be cured. GRAIL is focused on alleviating the global burden of cancer by developing pioneering technology to detect and identify multiple deadly cancer types early. The company is using the power of next-generation sequencing, population-scale clinical studies, and state-of-the-art computer science and data science to enhance the scientific understanding of cancer biology, and to develop its multi-cancer early detection blood test. Job Title: Data Analyst REMOTE FROM ANYWHERE IN THE USA
Job Description:
aytm “Ask Your Target Market” is hiring a Data Analyst specializing in data processing and research analytics to join our growing research services team. This position will assist in determining appropriate data processing needs for clients and execute data analysis associated with quantitative market research projects. The data analyst works with internal research team members, Account Management and Business Development teams to design and provide customized back-end deliverables either independently, or with vendor support.

About Us:
aytm delivers state-of-the-art insights automation technology and expert guidance that’s focused on providing answers for the clients of today, while evolving a platform that supports the curious of tomorrow. Advancing research with transparency and flexibility, aytm helps you connect to a community of people, optimize your products, positioning, and concepts, and get from idea to market faster. We have a world-class platform, top-tier clients, and a creative and energetic team.

We offer a Zero Commute, 100% remote work environment, flexible hours, a friendly and energizing Slack-connected team, competitive salary and top-notch benefits.

Responsibilities:
Work within the research services team to conduct full and partial service quantitative market research projects across numerous research methodologies and a diverse set of clients.
Execute data-centric deliverables including data manipulation (e.g., stacking, appends, weighting), custom data tables/crosstabs, interactive template-based deliverables (e.g., conjoint simulators), and data visualization and reporting.
Work closely with internal team members to ensure the smooth execution and on-time delivery of research services including programmed survey links, custom data tables, simulators, reports, and other deliverables.
Work directly with clients in an “Assisted-DIY” fashion, supporting AYTM end users by providing expert advising on advanced methodologies that are automated on the platform (e.g., choice-based conjoint, TURF, etc.), answering data and analysis questions, and executing one-off analysis requests as needed.
Serve as a knowledge resource to other internal teams, including Business Development/Account Management, Client Training, and Product Development.
Coordinate with external vendors for any back-end requirements
Work/communicate both as an individual and as part of a team in a matrixed environment

Qualifications:
Undergraduate degree in marketing, social sciences, mathematics or other related field, with a quantitative emphasis on statistics or research methods, or equivalent work experience.
3+ years client-facing experience in data processing as relates to quantitative market research on the supplier side.
Strong experience with data-intensive aspects of online survey research: programming, data analysis, data processing and advanced methodologies.
Skilled user of the Microsoft Office Suite, in particular Excel and PowerPoint.
Advanced proficiency in at least one data processing or statistical analysis software (example: Q, Quantum, SPSS, MarketSight, Decipher, IBM SurveyProfessional, R).
Advanced understanding of data structure, manipulation & storage, including best practices.
Ability to translate conceptual objectives into actionable data and analytics related tasks).
Experience using one or more online survey platforms. Experience with the aytm platform is preferred, but not required.
Strong written and verbal skills and should enjoy taking a consultative and collaborative approach – both with clients and fellow team members.

What we offer:
A work environment built around empathy, creativity, curiosity, organic growth and an abundance mindset. We’re a fun and vibrant group of people, dedicated to putting in the hard work to make a platform we are proud of, serving the needs of our clients with empathy, and making aytm an incredible place to work. We were recently awarded 2021 Inc 5000 Fastest-Growing Private Company and 2021 Inc Best Places to Work. We’re also fully virtually, which means you’ll be working remotely from the location of your choosing (home, coffee house, library). While being a Zero-commute company and providing you with an amazing level of freedom, convenience, and flexibility, it requires a certain inner discipline and capacity to be effective at a distance. Remote work experience is preferred, but not required..

Unlimited PTO - With a recommended minimum number of days taken each year
Affordable Insurance -$0 deductible Health plans plus dental, vision, and more!
401k retirement - Account with automatic company contributions

Responsibilities:
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand data requirements and identify key insights to be visualized.
Design and develop visually appealing and intuitive dashboards, reports, and interactive visualizations to present complex data in a clear and concise manner.
Utilize data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, QlikView) to create dynamic and interactive visualizations that allow users to explore data and uncover patterns and trends.
Work closely with data engineers and data scientists to ensure accurate and reliable data sources for visualization purposes.
Interpret data and provide insights to stakeholders through visualizations, enabling them to make informed decisions and take appropriate actions.
Conduct data analysis and validation to ensure the accuracy and integrity of data used for visualization.
Stay updated on industry best practices and emerging trends in data visualization and provide recommendations for continuous improvement.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand their needs and translate them into actionable visualization projects.
Qualifications:
Bachelor's degree in Business Administration, Computer Science, Information Systems, Economics, Finance, or a related field.
3 years of experience as a Data Analyst, with a specialization in creating visualizations.
Proficiency in data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, QlikView, or similar platforms.
Strong understanding of data visualization principles, best practices, and usability standards.
Solid knowledge of data analysis techniques, including data cleaning, transformation, and validation.
Proficient in SQL and data querying languages to extract and manipulate data.
Experience with programming languages such as Python or R is a plus.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a keen eye for detail and the ability to identify patterns and insights within data.
Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to effectively convey complex information to non-technical stakeholders.
Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment, manage multiple priorities, and meet deadlines.
Experience with data governance and data quality management is advantageous.

Within the Customer Experience Organization, the Digital Experience and Transformation Team delivers on ideas and technology, innovating to create frictionless experiences in owning and using HP products. The Data Analyst is a critical member of the core team that sets strategy, defines roadmap and prioritizes operational activities for solutions like our Virtual Assistant bot, Diagnostics and other self-service tools. This individual will drive improvements to performance and quality KPI’s and provide insights to the core team and key stakeholders. The successful candidate will create efficient algorithms to draw intelligence from existing large data sets, and effectively communicate results in relatable business language that drives action and results. Department Overview
Electric Asset Management is responsible for the electric system engineering and planning, asset strategy, and risk management across transmission, distribution, and substation asset families. This centralized, risk-informed approach allows PG&E to manage electric risk, asset and system health, interconnections, and performance by using consistent standards, work methods, prioritization, and program sponsorship, while leveraging lessons learned from inspections and asset data to inform asset management decisions. The organization is accountable for asset planning and strategy, standards and work methods, and asset data management for Electric.

The Asset Knowledge Management (AKM) team, within Electric Asset Management, is responsible for the management, quality, and access of PG&E’s electric asset data. The team’s objective is to maximize the use and ensure the trustworthiness of PG&E’s critical electric data assets.

Position Summary
The Expert Data Quality Analyst will be responsible for technical implementation of the Asset Data Quality (ADQ) program – a mission critical program launched in 2022 to systematically achieve and maintain the level of data quality required to support Electric Engineering Planning & Strategy’s business objectives, including regulatory compliance, risk management, improved operational efficiency, and advanced analytics. Program objectives include establishing a comprehensive inventory of PG&E’s critical electric asset-related data, capturing and maintaining metadata for all critical data, establishing and applying data quality rules to all critical data, and prioritizing data quality issues for remediation.

The Expert Data Quality Analyst will work at the direction of the ADQ Program Manager and partner with a cross-functional team composed of members from Electric Asset Knowledge Management, Electric Asset Management, Enterprise Data Management, Information Technology to implement the ADQ program. Responsibilities include leading the collection of metadata, development of data quality rules, guidance of data quality platform architecture decisions, conducting cause analysis regarding data quality rule violations, and supporting data quality remediation activities.

The near-term focus of ADQ will be on systematic measurement and improvement of PG&E’s electric Asset Registry and Asset Condition data. The ADQ program will expand its focus will shift to other data types that support Asset Management (e.g., event data, maintenance).

This position is hybrid, working from your remote office and your assigned work location based on business need. The assigned work location will be within the PG&E Service Territory.

PG&E is providing the salary range that the company in good faith believes it might pay for this position at the time of the job posting. Although, we estimate the successful candidate hired into this role will be placed towards the middle or entry point of the range, the decision will be made on a case-by-case basis related to these factors.

A reasonable salary range is:

Annual Minimum: $114 ,000.00
Annual Maximum: $182,000.00

Partner with lead Program Manager to implement Asset Data Quality (ADQ) programs to systematically inventory PG&E’s critical electric asset data, capture metadata, measure data quality, and drive the execution of high-priority data improvements.

Advise Program Manager on strategy and roadmap to reflect continuous improvement and expansion into data types beyond Asset Registry and Asset Condition data (e.g., event data)

Job Title: Employee Insights Data Analyst, Senior Associate
Job Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

Our Employee Insights team studies employee interactions, trends and changes to better understand our employees’ experiences. Usually, we begin with a question, challenge or idea related to our company’s workforce trends. Your role involves taking those hypotheses and determining how to best understand them through structured research and data analysis.
Your primary responsibility will be gathering, analyzing, and presenting data about employee experience and workforce trends, in partnership with key stakeholders to deliver unique insights about the organization.
This position reports to the VP of Reporting and Analytics and will be part of a team of problem solvers and solution designers dedicated to making Chase a great place to work.
Our job is to dig into the trends, changes and nuances that exist amongst Consumer and Community Banking’s global population. The journey often starts with a hypothesis or a question. Your job will be to collect, synthesize, and present data we need to dig in to key research topics, and to maintain responsibility for tracking and reporting on key metrics that inform senior leaders decision making processes.
Job Responsibilities:
Act as the voice of the employee by supporting the design and implementation of our listening strategy and by providing high quality employee insights that HR and Business Leaders can leverage to influence the employee experience
Conduct end-to-end analysis on large employee data sets to identify patterns/trends and answer questions/hypothesis about the employee experience and what influences it
Turn data into easy to understand visuals that tell a story. Make complex ideas simple so leaders can act on them
Be an expert project manager of all efforts you touch, delivering high quality work on time consistently
Ensure all appropriate data privacy, security, and controls requirements are incorporated into all processes
Maintain and expand partnerships with key stakeholders within the lines of business and at the firmwide level
Required Qualifications, capabilities and skills
5+ years of relevant work experience, preferably in a role involving extracting/ aggregating data and performing employee data analysis and storytelling
Advanced knowledge of analyzing both structured and unstructured data; managing and manipulate large data sets in Excel; quantitative and qualitative research
Ability to work to solve problems independently, remove barriers and propose solutions, i.e. taking a hypothesis, researching and coming back with a perspective
Ability to identify and communicate critical insights through appealing and concise reports and summaries
Strong partnership and consulting skills, ability to work with a variety of stakeholders and peers in order to get things done
Balance of intellectual curiosity with exceptional critical thinking, problem solving and analytical skills; ability to absorb and present complex ideas quickly and accurately
Preferred Qualifications, capabilities and skills
Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Statistics, Data Science, Industrial and Organizational Psychology, or other Behavioral Sciences
5+ years of specific HR systems experience
Experience with R, Python or other statistical programming languages/software, Business Intelligence software and/or data wrangling tools such as Alteryx
Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau or QlikView

Chase is a leading financial services firm, helping nearly half of America’s households and small businesses achieve their financial goals through a broad range of financial products. Our mission is to create engaged, lifelong relationships and put our customers at the heart of everything we do. We also help small businesses, nonprofits and cities grow, delivering solutions to solve all their financial needs.

As a part of our commitment to health and safety, we have implemented various COVID-related health and safety requirements for our workforce. Shadow Operations Data Analyst (Full/Part Time)
Position Responsibilities
This position contributes to the development and support of the RailPod inspection data collection and data validation process prior to customer review. This role includes the review and quality assessment of exception deviations that are found during live inspections by the fielded technology. In addition to day-to-day validation of data, you’ll provide initial systems troubleshooting and documentation prior to escalating the specific issue. If an issue does need to be escalated, you’ll act as the primary means of communication between the operator in the field and associated back office support teams that can help address and troubleshoot the specific issue. You will collaborate with team members to process additional requests from the customer, coordinate logistical scheduling, create/edit process documentation, and assist with the collection and organizing of internal data. This position requires a high bandwidth internet connection and requires the individual to be working with a computer for 8-10 hours per day. As RailPod runs inspections for customers across different time zones, shadow operators must be available to support live inspections at varying start times regardless of their location. Nighttime inspections for certain customers will comprise around ⅓ of overall inspections that will be run, which may require live support between 11pm-4am EST. It will not be expected that if you work during this nighttime window that you would also support daytime operations the following day.
Qualifications
Requirements for the role include the following:

A pioneer in K–12 education since 2000, Amplify is leading the way in next-generation curriculum and assessment. For more information, visit amplify.com.
As a member of the engineering organization at Amplify, you will join a dedicated team taking on the most challenging problems in education with the best ideas in technology – including user experience, APIs and services, data analysis, and deployment pipelines. Our data analytics teams ingest, transform, model, and aggregate the data that empowers teams across Amplify and our customers to make sense of and tell stories with their data. We believe strongly in teaching our teammates to serve themselves, within a safe, reliable, and agile data environment. You’ll be building analytical solutions but also the sharing-and-learning culture so that every team uses your analysis to improve their own lives and those of our students and teachers

Ability to learn and adopt new tools and methods

Proficient in a statistical or functional programming language (preferably Python or R)

The Texas Department of Family and Protective Services (DFPS) is currently seeking a Data Analyst within the Chief Technology Office (CTO) team of ITS Department to perform advanced data analysis, research and data governance work.

Performs advanced data systems analysis, research and data governance work. Work involves coordinating the planning and analysis of data modeling; conducting detailed analysis of and extensive research on data, providing results to implement and manage database systems, data warehouses, and data analytics, ensuring data quality; and working in a team environment in designing strategies and setting standards for development, operations and programming.

The mission of DFPS is to protect children, the elderly, and people with disabilities from abuse, neglect, and exploitation by involving clients, families, and communities. We are looking to grow our teams with people who share our energy and enthusiasm to get behind our mission of protecting those among us who are most in need.
The Data Analyst works under minimal supervision, with considerable latitude for the use initiative and independent judgement.

Analyzes data using standard statistical tools, methods, and techniques.

Consults with internal and external customers to identify user needs.

Compiles and queries data.

Identifies data gaps, errors, anomalies, inconsistencies, and redundancies by analyzing the content, structure, and relationships within data.

Cleans and prunes data to discard irrelevant information.

Prepares concise, comprehensive technical reports to present and interpret data, identify alternatives, and make and justify recommendations on data revisions.

Assists in defining, developing, and implementing data standards. Assists in developing data quality measures, analyzing data quality results, and implementing necessary changes to ensure data quality improvement.

A Healthcare SQL Data Analyst is a professional who works with healthcare data to extract, analyze, and interpret valuable insights that can inform decision-making and improve patient care within the healthcare industry. This role combines expertise in both SQL (Structured Query Language) and healthcare domain knowledge.

Key responsibilities and tasks:
1. Data Extraction and Collection: Gathering healthcare data from various sources, such as electronic health records (EHRs), billing systems, claims databases, and other healthcare-related datasets.

2. Data Cleansing and Transformation: Cleaning and preparing the collected data for analysis by identifying and addressing data quality issues, missing values, duplicates, and inconsistencies. Transforming raw data into a structured format suitable for analysis.

3. Database Management: Creating and managing relational databases to store and organize healthcare data efficiently. This includes designing database schemas, tables, and optimizing data storage for performance.

4. SQL Querying: Writing complex SQL queries to extract relevant information from databases. This might involve joining multiple tables, filtering data, aggregating results, and creating calculated fields.

5. Data Analysis: Applying statistical and analytical techniques to healthcare data to uncover patterns, trends, and insights. This could involve performing descriptive statistics, data profiling, and creating visualizations to present findings.

6. Performance Monitoring: Monitoring the performance of healthcare systems and processes by analyzing relevant data. This could include tracking patient outcomes, hospital admissions, readmission rates, and other key performance indicators.

7. Predictive Modeling: Building predictive models using healthcare data to forecast outcomes, such as patient readmissions, disease progression, or resource utilization. These models can aid in decision-making and resource allocation.

8. Healthcare Reporting: Creating regular reports and dashboards that provide insights to healthcare providers, administrators, and other stakeholders. These reports might focus on clinical outcomes, financial performance, and operational efficiency.

9. Compliance and Privacy: Ensuring that all data handling and analysis processes comply with healthcare regulations (such as HIPAA in the United States) and maintain patient privacy and confidentiality.

10. Collaboration: Collaborating with healthcare professionals, data scientists, IT teams, and other stakeholders to understand data needs, interpret findings, and develop data-driven strategies.

11. Continuous Learning: Staying updated on the latest developments in both the healthcare industry and data analytics to ensure the application of best practices and innovative techniques.

Importantly, our solutions are designed specifically for Medicaid and lower-income Medicare beneficiaries, and we meet our members where they are, bringing care into the home and neighborhoods through our community-based care teams and Virtual Care offerings.

Under direction from the Director of Analytics and Institutional Research, Data Analysts at the College of Southern Idaho (CSI) support a campus-wide data-informed decision-making culture. By querying data and creating reports, the Data Analyst provides insights that help the business make decisions. The Data Analyst also looks for patterns in the data that can improve student outcomes and increase the CSI’s student body through retention and recruiting analytics.

THIS IS NOT A REMOTE POSITION, AND THE SUCCESSFUL APPLICANT WILL BE WORKING ON CAMPUS IN TWIN FALLS, IDAHO.

The Data Analysts are responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting on data from various internal and external sources. They know how to validate data and find data integrity issues that arise during the data cleaning process. Analysts provide BI solutions and use reporting techniques that adhere to sound research principles.

Proactively developing and maintaining good relationships with stakeholders across the organization is essential for Data Analysts. They need to deliver quality solutions that meet their stakeholders’ expectations. This requires working independently, collaborating, and engaging within the college’s institutional effectiveness (IE) team with administrators, faculty, and staff from across the college.

Analysts should be curious, critical thinkers who desire to develop and enhance their technical skillset. Successful analysts can balance a high-level perspective of business problems with the technical details needed to provide solutions. They demonstrate some degree of “business sense,” with the ability to think in terms of the administrators they are assisting while at the same time maintaining a more in-depth understanding of the data and related technical components needed to address the problem.

Data Analyst Duties & Responsibilities

Project requirements vary but will likely require a combination of some or all of the following:

Support a campus-wide data-informed decision-making culture.
Work with stakeholders to establish and define actionable research questions.
Implement actionable analytics with a focus on recruiting and retention efforts.
Create and organize various student contact lists, allowing CSI staff to execute strategic student outreach effectively.
Build and maintain business intelligence reports and dashboards.
Anticipate the need for and suggest reports and queries relating to the institutional mission.
Compile, analyze, and report institutional data related to various student and institutional characteristics.
Research, organize, and assemble data retrieved from various local, state, and national databases.
Manage survey projects from design through analysis and reporting.
Produce actionable insights from data through various quantitative and qualitative analytics.
Develop presentations and visualizations that effectively communicate report outcomes and key findings.

Collaboration and teamwork
Exemplify quality customer service, client relations, and time management.
Handle correspondence and communications in a professional and timely manner.
Work effectively both independently and collaboratively with colleagues.
Actively participate in weekly Institutional Research meetings to discuss current projects, challenges, and successes.
Collaborate with Institutional Technology (IT) and other stakeholders across the institutions to define business processes that maintain and enhance data integrity.
Emphasize reproducibility of research through thorough documentation and transparency.

Additional responsibilities
Engage in consistent learning, development, and improvement.
Identify and master new technical tools and techniques that enhance department skill sets.
Maintain office files, records, and software logs, emphasizing reproducibility.
Perform other miscellaneous and special duties as assigned.

Required Qualifications/Skills

Education and Experience
Hold an associate’s degree in business, analytics, economics, finance, or a related field.
Have at least one year of relevant experience, which can include internships, extracurricular activities, or volunteer work.
Technical Knowledge
Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite (Outlook, Word, PowerPoint, Excel).
Proficiency with Power BI
Functional skills with SQL (e.g., filtering, using the HAVING clause, and merging data using inner and outer joins)
Basic statistics.
Interpersonal Skills
Ability to work in both team and independent work environments.
Excellent communication and client management skills.

Technical Knowledge or Experience in:
Relational databases
Other computing languages (s) (e.g. R, Python, C#)
Knowledge of the College of Southern Idaho’s implemented software:
Microsoft SQL Server
Business Intelligence (Power BI, SSRS)
R Studio
Anthology/Campus Management (ERP, SIS, CRM)
Office 365

Occasional evening or weekend work to meet reporting deadlines.

Skilled user of the Microsoft Office Suite, in particular Excel and PowerPoint.

Advanced understanding of data structure, manipulation & storage, including best practices.

Strong written and verbal skills and should enjoy taking a consultative and collaborative approach – both with clients and fellow team members.

The primary responsibilities of this role are to acquire, analyze, compile, evaluate, and review data for use in standard products, non-standard products, and/or data holdings in support of mission requirements.
Duties & Responsibilities
Processing, analysis, evaluation and exploitation of navigation, remote sensor, and shipboard instrumentation data collected from various deep ocean systems.
The candidate will be involved in pre-mission support, data collection, analyst & evaluation, and report generation.
As enhanced data is identified, the candidate will be responsible to update and correct data sets.
Perform analysis and evaluation of imagery collected from side scan sonar, bathometric, video, and still photography cameras.
Use proprietary software including GIS-based systems in a network of workstations and personal computers (Windows) to perform basic imaging enhancement, display, and analytical functions to obtain, organize, and present information relevant to the exploitation of remotely sensed and imaged data obtained from deep ocean systems.
Review mission related data logs, worksheets, and reports to determine focal points for the analysis as well as discovery of deficiencies and discrepancies in the performance of data collection equipment and systems.
Preparation of formal written technical reports as well as oral briefs to report analysis findings and conclusions to the customer.
Schedule can be demanding throughout the year and work outside normal working hours from time to time should be anticipated.
Travel is required. Will be required to participate in at sea exercises or data collection missions of various durations. Durations normally are between 30-60 days but can be as much as 90 days. Normal annual requirement is 120 days.
Represent OTECH and our customer by interacting and participating in meetings, panels, and committees within Department of Defense, Department of the Navy, and Intelligence Community in the capital planning process
Production of various ad hoc documentation & deliverables.
Maintain configuration control thereby ensuring precise data records.
Support program reviews and technical reviews of various documentation deliverables.
Qualifications

REQUIRED
Associate degree in a technical or related field. Equivalent work experience may be considered in lieu of degree.
Minimum three to five years of related experience.
Background in GIS products (ESRI) and Side Look Sonars (SLS) processing.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office, including Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, and Excel.
Ability to obtain and maintain a DoD security clearance is required. Must hold/acquire a TS/SCI with Polygraph.
Strong written and verbal communication skills.
Must be able to prioritize tasks and work independently and in team settings.
Ability to pass and maintain a maritime physical. Must take maritime safety training IAW the US coast guard guidelines and meet physical, dental, and regional immunization requirements.
DESIRED
Bachelor’s degree in Oceanography, Underwater Archeology, or related field.
Experience with Autonomous Underwater Vehicle (AUV), & Remotely Operated Vehicles (ROVs) and their support equipment.
Experience with SLS systems, Doppler Sonars, Navigation & underwater cameras equipment.
Knowledge of products like SonarWiz, Hypack and WinFrog.
Equal Opportunity Employer

Job Summary:
Premier Franchise Management is actively looking for a competent and highly detailed Data Analyst to work full-time in our Franklin, Tennessee location. The ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of financial principles and excel in providing analytical and data-oriented support to our Premier family. The essential functions of this role will be finding insights in large datasets, synthesizing, and communicating results to drive business results and growth. This person will work cross-functionally with the Finance, Accounting, Sales, and Operations Departments. This position requires a successful candidate to be a self-starter, managing and providing consistent and reliable reporting and analysis, in addition to utilizing primary and secondary research methods.
Job Responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics, and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and quality.
Acquire data from internal and external sources to construct varying standardized reporting and dashboarding for utilization by the Executive Leadership Team and other stakeholders.
Filter and “clean” data by developing and reviewing variance reports, period-over-period analyses, and performance indicators.
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends and patterns in complex data sets.
Provide analytical reporting to identify key market trends and insights.
Work with the management team to prioritize business data and information needs.
Monitor performance and quality control plans to identify improvements.
Ideal candidate will possess:
Strong time-management skills and an ability to organize and coordinate multiple concurrent projects.
Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, PowerBI, Tableau, and an aptitude for learning new software and systems.
Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, and segmentation techniques.
Strong knowledge of financial reporting packages, databases, understanding of programming language(s), with the ability to run queries, write reports, and present findings with strong data and graphs.
Ability to maintain the confidentiality of information related to the company and its employees.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills.
Highest attention to detail and accuracy with creative critical thinking and problem-solving skills.
Coachability, friendly demeanor, and willingness to demonstrate ownership of job and department functions within our company while also being an amazing team member to the rest of our PFM Family!
Position Details:
This position is based in the Finance/Accounting department reporting to the Financial Planning & Analysis Manager. Role is full-time, exempt salaried at our Franklin, Tennessee location. Schedule is day shift Monday – Friday, with additional flexibility needed around important deadlines or cutoffs. We offer a full comprehensive benefit package to include Medical, Dental, Vision, Life insurances; Paid Time Off; Sick Time; and 401(k) retirement plan.
About Premier Franchise Management
For over 30 years, the Premier brand has been making swimming pool dreams become reality. We Build and Service residential pools and spas nationwide with over 160 locations across the United States. Premier Franchise Management is the Franchisor for all our locations and provides support to help grow each individual business in hopes to grow the brand internationally into the future!
Company Culture – every individual that works for the Premier brand is an extension of our family. Our exciting culture and family values are the utmost important mission. From the CEO to our franchise pool builders, everyone is treated with the highest level of respect and held to the greatest level of standards in their work and how they carry themselves both personally and professionally.
Core Values – from a humble background, our CEO has built this organization off strict core values to carry the continuance of our company culture into every home we enter to build a pool. These values are as follows:
Integrity. The quality of being honest and having strong moral principles – 100% honest, 100% of the time!
Work Ethic. The principle that hard work is intrinsically virtuous or worthy of reward – Give your customers, your company, and your co-workers maximum effort…everyday!
Team Player. The ability to put aside your personal goals and work well with your co-workers towards a common goal – Support and work together with everyone within the organization!
Accountability. The willingness to accept responsibility for one’s actions – Acknowledge your mistakes, learn from them and commit to ensuring the same mistakes do not reoccur!
Quality of Work. All work shall be performed in a professional manner in accordance with the predetermined specifications, and expectations – Ensure that your work is completed promptly and void of error!

GitHub helps companies and organizations succeed by allowing them to build better software, together. We are looking for an experienced Product Data Analyst to lead strategic planning, development, and execution of product data and insights initiatives across our GitHub Product organization. This role will sit within the Business Planning team and provide dedicated support to our Chief Product Officer.
As the Product Data Analyst, you will be responsible for building out our Product profitability framework and taxonomy structure to measure the performance and health of individual Product lines. You will work closely cross-functionally with sales, product management, strategic finance, data operations, and engineering to gather, analyze, and integrate data to support informed decision-making for the executive leadership team.

Responsibilities
Product Health Reporting
Develop and implement a portfolio-wide product profitability framework and taxonomy structure that aligns with GitHub's financial objectives and enables effective measurement and analysis of product performance.
Identify and define key performance indicators (KPIs) and metrics to assess the financial performance of GitHub's products establishing reporting mechanisms to monitor progress and bring actionable insights to drive business results.
Collaborate with product management and finance teams to gather requirements and ensure the accuracy, integrity, and consistency of financial data related to product profitability.
Data Analysis and Insights
Partner closely with GitHub’s product, sales, customer, and finance data teams to collect, validate, and analyze financial and usage data from various data sources to identify trends, patterns, and opportunities for optimizing product profitability.
Develop and maintain comprehensive reporting, dashboards, and visualizations that provide insights and recommendations to senior management and product stakeholders.
Conduct in-depth analysis including modeling and forecasting to support strategic decision-making related to product pricing, cost optimization, and resource allocation.
Provide data-driven recommendations to optimize product profitability, identify areas of improvement, and drive operational efficiencies across Product teams.
Data Governance and Management
Establish and maintain data governance policies, standards, and procedures to ensure the accuracy, integrity, and security of financial data.
Monitor data quality and consistency, identify and resolve data issues, and implement controls to prevent data errors and discrepancies.
Collaborate with the Data Operations team to implement and maintain appropriate data infrastructure, tooling, and access to support business intelligence initiatives related to product profitability.
Required Qualifications
Minimum 5+ years experience in business intelligence, financial analysis, or data related roles retrieving, analyzing and manipulating large datasets with SQL queries.
Prior experience with Power BI or high proficiency in other data analytics tools.
Experience collaborating with cross-functional teams across many different stakeholders and senior leaders.
Preferred Qualifications
General understanding of business practice, financial principles and product strategy.
Strong business acumen and ability to influence key stakeholders to make data-driven decisions across both Product and GTM functions.
Excellent communication skills with ability to quickly turnaround complex tasks.
Ability to analyze data, track patterns, and identify trends that impact business performance.

SmarterTravel’s Leadership Principles
Take Big Swings - Thinking small is a self-fulfilling prophecy. Leaders strive to spend their time exclusively on what’s important, and they shed the rest. They seek out the highest return on their team’s time and effort.
Data Driven - Leaders work backwards from the solution to generate plans. They use data to be sure their time and effort are always leveraged at the most impactful work. They admit when they are wrong and use the data to eliminate their blind spots.
Make Moonshine - Leaders create value from spare and under-utilized parts. They’re resourceful and tenacious. They expect and require innovation and invention from their teams, and they find ways to simplify. They are situationally aware; they look for good ideas from anywhere.
Insist on the Highest Standards - Leaders keep the standards relentlessly high. They demand high quality products, services, and processes because they deliver high quality products, services, and processes. Leaders solve root problems and ensure that when problems get fixed, they stay fixed.
Bias for Action - Leaders run everywhere they go. Many decisions and actions are reversible and don’t need extensive study. Leaders value calculated risk taking because they know that in business, speed wins.
Have Integrity; Earn Trust - Leaders listen attentively, speak candidly, and treat others respectfully. They are vocally self-critical, even when doing so is difficult or embarrassing. Leaders are not arrogant. They benchmark themselves against the best and identify their gaps.
Hire and Develop the Best - Leaders raise the bar with every hire and promotion. They want to work with other leaders. They recognize exceptional talent and enthusiastically propel them throughout the organization. Leaders are serious about their role in coaching others.
Ownership - Leaders think long-term and don’t sacrifice long-term value for short-term results. They own all the inputs to their business. They act on behalf of the entire company, beyond just their own team.
Disagree and Commit - Leaders respectfully challenge decisions when they disagree, even when doing so is uncomfortable or awkward. They have conviction; they do not compromise in the name of social niceties. Once a decision is reached, they commit wholly.
Dive Deep - Leaders operate at once with immense perspective and granular detail. No task is beneath them. They audit frequently, and they are skeptical when metrics and anecdote differ.
Deliver Results - Leaders focus their time on the key drivers for their business. They pursue them obsessively to deliver results with the right quality and in a timely fashion. They rise to the occasion and never compromise.

Professional standards expected of all employees:

Professionally interacts and maintains effective and open communication with all personnel, vendors/manufacturers and customers
Maintains a professional and positive manner and appearance at all times
Performs all duties safely and in a manner consistent with the policies and procedures of SmarterTravel
Adheres to all applicable department, production, and company related Operational, Safety and Human Resources policies and procedures
Performs all duties as assigned
